<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no" ?>
<FinalDraft DocumentType="Script" Template="No" Version="3">

  <Content>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text>Fade IN:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="1" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 6/8" Page="1" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="FRANKIE J"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. atlanta Radio station - late night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>MUSIC TREATMENT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>TONY </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">SINCLAIR</Text>
      <Text>, the overnight shift DJ at a top Atlanta radio station, is spitting out the hits. He takes a SIP from his cup, not sure if it’s coffee; but he’s feeling no pain and enjoying his session.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Tony</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re listening to V-105.5, the station that brings you a taste of EVERYTHING!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That was a slamming hit from Bell, Biv, Devo, called Poison.  That’s right ya’ll; never trust a big butt and a smile. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">(Sotto</Text>
      <Text> Voce)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I know that’s right.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He’s about to wrap up his shift, when WE SEE, Frankie J, the morning superstar DJ; coming into view.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Well, my time is almost up and we’re about to turn it over to Frankie J, the number one DJ in Atlanta.  Frankie will be waking you up with everything you need and a little bit more.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Frankie eats this attention up and has a big SMILE.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m gonna wrap this thing up with my theme song; Last Night A DJ Saved My Life.  So watch out for those energy vampires.  You know, hurt people hurt people.  So always in parting, worry about nothing, pray about anything and thank God for everything.  This is your lover boy Tony Sinclair signing out.  </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s V-105.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He’s out.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Frankie j</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(giving Tony a High Five)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Boy, you were hotter than fish grease.I was listening to you on the way in.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thanks man.  I’m glad you liked it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>FRANKIE J</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Liked it?  Man, I loved it!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m telling ya Tony, you’re going places.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I wish my pay check was saying that. I want that paid,..paid money like you got. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, I want to be like you, Uncle Frank.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>FRANKIE J</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(smiling)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Boy, you crazy.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m serious.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>FRANKIE J</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Just keep doing what you doing.  Your time will come.  Hell, I didn’t get here overnight.  It’s called paying your dues.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(packing up his gear)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, I hear ya. I still want what you got, Uncle Frank. I don’t wanna play ball no more.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They give each other DAP, while Frankie gets settled in to start doing his thing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="2" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="2" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. COVERED PARKING LOT - EARLY MORNING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony is coming into view.  WE SEE a Porche and a Ford Fairmont parked side by side.  Tony crosses to the driver side of the Porche, looking in; then OPENS the passenger door to the Fairmont and SLIDES over to the driver side.  He SHAKES his head, as he looks at the Porche one more time.  His eyes say it all.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="3" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 5/8" Page="3" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHRISTINE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. tony’s apartment - earLY MORNING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A tired Tony slowly walks into his modest apartment, dropping down his gear and heads towards the bedroom. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>INT. TONY’S BEDROOM - EARLY MORNING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He’s met at the bedroom door by Christine, his girlfriend, who’s BRUSHING her teeth.  </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ToNY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(trying to get a kiss)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey baby.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She MOTIONS away from him; while still BRUSHING her teeth and heading back into the bathroom.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Christine (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s about time you got here.  Why you so late!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What are you talking about?  I came home straight from the station.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She rinses out her mouth and comes out of the bathroom.  Tony tries to show some affection.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(trying for a hug)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Give me a kiss now; since you got rid of the morning breath.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(pulling away)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You haven’t gotten rid of the late night breath. And I need to talk to you about something.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This shift you’re working.  The only time I see you is on my way to work and when your ass is getting ready for work. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This ain’t working and you need to start bringing some more money up in this camp.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Don’t start bugging like that Christine, I just got in.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Damn.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(holding a stack of bills)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Well, this didn’t just get in.  </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s this?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s called a light bill, gas bill, internet bill.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Gas bill?  This is a totally electric apartment.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You know what I’m talking about, Tony.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What are you talking about?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She GRABS her purse and coat.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>If I have to tell you, then don’t worry about it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She SLAMS the door, leaving Tony with a blank and confused look.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="4" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="4" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHRISTINE"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Tony’s bedroom - niGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony’s alarm BLARES from his cell phone.  It’s time for work and Christine is fast asleep.  Tony is feeling a Love Jones; so he tries for a quickie love session before work.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(not in the mood)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Stop it, Tony!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He tries even harder.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tony, stop it!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A saddened Tony rises from the bed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="5" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2" Page="5" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHRISTINE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="FEMALE CALLER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. RADIO STATION - LATE NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>MUSIC TREATMENT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>It’s the slow jam time and Tony is also doing a call in and advice session with his listeners.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re listening to the quiet storm, with your main man, Tony Sinclair.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Let’s take another call.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>PUNCHING in a caller.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re on the air with Tony Sinclair; what’s on you mind?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>It’s a female caller.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Female caller (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>Hi Tony, am I on the air?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes love. What’s your question?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>FEMALE CALLER (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Well, I’ve been in a relationship with this guy for quite sometime; and it just doesn’t seem to be working.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What do you mean?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>FEMALE CALLER (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I mean, it seems like we’re in two different places.  The only thing it seems he wants from me now is just some,...you know.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, I feel ya.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>FEMALE CALLER (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I just want to know if you think I should stay in this kind of relationship or move on?  I just don’t feel anything when he touches me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Well, if you feel that way, then maybe it’s time to move on.  It’s no way you should stay if you’re not feeling it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>FEMALE CALLER (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You think so?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I know so.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>FEMALE CALLER (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(with tears in her voice)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thank you so much Tony.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re welcome, baby. Just hang in there. It’ll be alright.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She HANGS UP and Tony takes the next call.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ToNY (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re on the night shift with Tony Sinclair. What can I do for you?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>This is a caller Tony knows; it’s his girlfriend, Christine.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tony, it’s Christine.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You mean my Christine?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey ya’ll, the love of my life; My girl Christine is calling up to give me a shout out. What’s up, baby!?! </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You know how you just told that last caller to move on?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We have a CROSSCUT of Christine at their apartment and Tony on the air.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="6" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="7" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHRISTINE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. TONY'S APRTMENT - Late Night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(packing her things)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Well, I’m doing the same thing.  It’s over.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What!?!  Baby stop playing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Christine GRABS her things.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m gone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text>Back To:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="7" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="7" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. Radio STATION - Late Night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony, still on the air, as we HEAR Christine closing the door and ending the call.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(in disbelief)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Baby, stop playing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We HEAR a dial tone and see the shocked look on Tony’s face as he’s being dumped on the air.  We CUT TO shots of his LISTENERS all over the city taking all of this in.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="8" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="7" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. Waffle House - Late Night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A CUSTOMER stops with a spoonful of food halfway to his mouth, a look of surprise on his face.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="9" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="7" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Laundry Mat - Late Night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A LADY bursts out laughing as she fills her dryer up.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="10" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="7" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Car - Late Night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>TEENS in their car drinking and smoking a joint, while choking on the smoke.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text>BACK TO:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="11" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="8" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. RaDIO STATION - Late NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Then back to Tony, in total shock.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text>CUT TO:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="12" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 1/8" Page="8" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHRISTINE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="LADY #1"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="LADY #3"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="SECURITY GUARD"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. HOT NIGHT CLUB - two years later - NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>MUSIC TREATMENT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We’re at a very hot night club, where the crowd is overflowing around the corner. All of Atlanta’s beautiful people are there and SECURITY is handling the CROWD. A group of beautiful LADIES are trying to get in.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>LADY #1 </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Security Guard)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do I have to stand in this line?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Security Guard</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s moving.  </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The second LADY in the line is Christine; Tony’s old girlfriend.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to the Security Guard)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Don’t I know you?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>SECURITY GUARD</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>A lot of people know me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A VIP is coming through and the Security Guard, MOVES Christine and her friends out of the way. She’s not happy.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey, you don’t have to move me,...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>SECURITY GUARD</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Obviously, I do.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Suddenly, WE SEE a very expensive car coming into view, which stops at the Valet area.  A new, polished and well dressed Tony Sinclair, POPS out, with a lot of swagger. Security knows who he is and makes a way from him through the CROWD, while he passes Christine and her crew, without even noticing her. She’s totally taken aback. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>LADY #1</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Christine)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s Tony Sinclair from V-105.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Didn’t you usta go with him?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Christine’s sick face says it all.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>LADY #3</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Girl, you messed up.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>LADY #1</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(agreeing)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Bad.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Christine face shows even more pain.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="13" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="4 5/8" Page="9" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHERYL"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DJ"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="GROUPIE #1"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="GROUPIE #2"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KISHA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WAITER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="YOUNG LADY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Hot nightclub vip area - nIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>MUSIC TREATMENT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony is making his way to his table in VIP. He’s noticed by the DJ.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DJ (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The man of the hour has just arrived. V105.5’s hot jock,      Mr. Tony Sinclair.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The CROWD goes wild, as Tony humberly takes in all of the love. He’s met at his table by his best friend Ken and his girl, Cheryl.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Ken</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(rising from the table with a hug)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s up, boy?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You got it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat and giving Cheryl a hug)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey baby.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Cheryl</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You smell good; always wearing the best oils.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text></Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(taking in the fragrance)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>  Is that Golden Sandalwood?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No,...Black Oudh.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I remember when he couldn’t afford Ole Spice. Your ass done come up, huh?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Get off my woman!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They LAUGH and take in a HUG.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ve been blessed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Listen at him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Suddenly, a few GROUPIES try to make their way over to the table.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Groupie #1</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(showing all of her goodies)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tony, Tony.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>GrouPIE #2</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(trying to sing)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I would have been in love by now, if it wasn’t for you, Tony.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony WAIVES with a smile, as Security moves them away from the area.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You like that, don’t ya?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s cool, but I’d love to have what you and Cheryl have.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cheryl smiles, then shows off something new on her finger.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Ah hell!  Is that what I think it is!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cheryl SMILES and Ken SMILES even more.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s what’s up!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They all HUG.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Where’s Darien?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERYL</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text></Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(looking at the dance floor)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>There he is.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>WE SEE Darien, blazing the dance floor, with a buck wild young lady.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Who’s that with him?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s his latest flavor, Kisha.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>How many flavors does he have?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>How many days of the week?  Then twice, no three times that many.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ToNY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>See that’s what I’m talking about.  I can’t do that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The music dies down. Darien and Kisha find their way over to the table.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Darien</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(giving Tony a HUG)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s up, boy!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You got it, man.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This is my new friend girl, Kisha.  Kisha, this is,...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Kisha</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(jumping in and very excited)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I know who you are!  You’re Tony Sinclair from V105.5!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>One of her breast almost falls out of her extremely tight dress top, as she tries to put it back in.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Tony)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>She fine as hell; dumb as hell too.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s how you like um, bro?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Darien SMILES.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Where’d you meet her, on your route?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah.  She works at a nail shop on Glenwood.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ToNY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh, okay.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(giving him DAP)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s what’s up!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Everyone is now seated and the WAITER brings over menus.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Waiter</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Would you like to start with an appetizer?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Cheryl)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What do you want honey?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERYL</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’d love some crab cakes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That sounds good. I think I’ll have the same.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAITER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Kisha)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And you, ma’am?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KISHA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(looking at the menu)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Ya’ll got Buffalo Wings, with Blue Cheese, no Ranch? Yeah, that’s what I want.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, hook me up with the same thing. A twenty piece.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat, to Tony)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The radio station picking this up, right?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony gives him a look.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ll take the house salad with a lite vinaigrette on the side.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to the Waiter)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hold bro, make that a ten piece.  </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">(Sotto</Text>
      <Text> voce)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The station must not be taking care of this; If he eating salad.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We FLASH CUT to the end of the meal and the Waiter is bringing over the desert tray.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WaiTER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Tony’s table)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do you see anything you’d like?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Suddenly, Security allows what appears to be the most beautiful LADY in the place, into the VIP area. All of the guys are speechless.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tony. Do you know her?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Nah, man. I wish I did.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>She’s coming over here.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>This lovely beauty has made her way to their table.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Young lady</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Excuse me, Mr. Sinclair.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>YOUNG LADY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Could I speak to you for a moment in private?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Darien CHOKES on his drink. Kisha PATS him on his back, while Tony is speechless. Ken POKES him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Ah, yes. Yes, you can.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony crosses from the table as they look for a quiet place.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="14" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 6/8" Page="14" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="YOUNG LADY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Quiet area near nightClub bathroom - nIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony and the young lady are alone in this quiet area near the bathroom. She suddenly gives him a big HUG and a KISS. Tony can’t believe what’s happening.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(trying to resist her affections)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wait a minute, baby. Do I know you like that? You trying to get with me?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>YOUNG LADY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You don’t know who I am; do you?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I wish I did.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>YOUNG LADY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>About two years ago, you saved my life.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I did what?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>YOUNG LADY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m Robin.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Robin? I don’t know anybody named Robin.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Robin</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do you remember the night your girlfriend broke up with you on the radio?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(with a sad look)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>How can I forget.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m the person that called in right before she did.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You kidding right?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No, I’m very serious.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Stop playing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>See, I was in a very bad relationship and I was struggling with leaving, until you gave me the advice and courage to leave.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I did that?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, you did that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t know what to say.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I want you to say you’ll have dinner with me or something; To let me show you how much I appreciate what you did for me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You don’t have to do that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(reaching in her purse)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Here’s my card. Please call me, okay?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(giving her his card)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I will.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She gives him another HUG and a tender KISS. Tony is in a daze, as he watches this true vision leave him standing there.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="15" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="7/8" Page="15" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="SADE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Tony’S APaRTMENT hallway - niGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony’s approaching his door after a long night of partying. He puts his key in lock, when SADE, his neighbor, pops out her door with a bottle of wine and two glasses; one of which she’s already drinking from.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Sade</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(kind of faded)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey, neighbor. What’s going on?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(like the British Singer)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Sharde’</Text>
      <Text>.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>SADE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I keep telling you, that’s the singer. Hell, I’m from Alabama. My name is Sade.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(taking a sip)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You want some wine?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No, I’m good.  </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>SADE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(being very sexy)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You want anything else?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Girl, stop playing like that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>SADE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(holding the wine bottle very sexy)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m not playing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Nah, I’m good.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>SADE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You sure are.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She gives him a sexy look and closes her door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="16" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="16" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. TONY’S APaRTMENT - Jacuzzi - late NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony is chilling in his jacuzzi tub trying to relax from his wild night.  </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="17" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="16" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. Radio STATION - FLAShback</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony in the studio alone doing it all: answering phones while editing an interview and on the air giving </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">giving</Text>
      <Text> out tickets to upcoming concert.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="18" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="16" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Tony'S apartmENT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony and Christine have another heated and foolish argument.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="19" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="16" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. Radio sTATION</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The night Christine broke up with Tony plays out again in a surreal fashion -- It’s like a Tony from an alternate universe is in the room watching it all play out again. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The board lights up as phone calls pour into the station.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="20" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="17" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. TonY'S APRTMENT - jacuzzi - present</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony’s cell phone RINGS, bringing </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">himb</Text>
      <Text> back to reality.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>It’s Darien.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="21" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2" Page="17" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Tony’s apartment jacuzzi - late night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s up player!?! You got one of them freaks over there?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>SHEBA, Tony’s cat, tries to rub up against his neck.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Get back, Sheba.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sheba? Ah, you got a new freak.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Nah, man. That’s my cat.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, I forgot - that’s the only pussy you got in your life since Christine left.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What do you want Darien?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony’s gets another call.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ma hit you right back.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I just dropped off Kisha. I’m going get these other two freaks and bring em by your house.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Why not your place?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Momma’s boyfriend over tonight.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The other line BEEPS again.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ma hit you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Call me back!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony clicks over.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hello?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hi, Tony. Are you asleep? This is Robin from tonight.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Robin!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I hope it’s not a bad time?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(rising from the tub)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No, no, I’m good. What’s going on?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I just wanted to thank you once again for all you’ve done. And I really do want to take you out for dinner.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey, I don’t feel like I’ve done anything.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You just don’t know.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do you like the Cheesecake Factory on </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Peachtree</Text>
      <Text>?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>How about I meet you there Friday night, around eight?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I have to check my schedule... </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text></Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text></Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="General">
      <Text>Tony pauses as if he’s really doing it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Tony (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Okay, see you then.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Great! I guess you will. Bye.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony SLIDES under the water in his tub.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="22" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="7/8" Page="19" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MARIO"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOOTHPICK"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Ext. Streets of buckhead - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Expensive sports car with dark windows come into view. Inside are two dope dealers, MARIO and TOOTHPICK. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Toothpick is behind the wheel and Mario is hitting a blunt.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Toothpick</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Damn, man; you smoking up more product than you selling.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Mario</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(with a New York accent)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Damn, son. You know who you talking to?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TOOTHPICK</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I know I’m about to cap your ass, if you don’t stop smoking up all the stash.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Mario</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We going to the Cheesecake Factory, right?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TOOTHPICK</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Right, right.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Mario</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m just trying to get ready for some of that sweet </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">sweet</Text>
      <Text>.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TOOTHPICK</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(pulling out his gun)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You gonna be tasting the end of this </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">glock</Text>
      <Text> in a minute.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Mario</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(pulling on the blunt)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Chill. I heard you twice the first time.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="23" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="6/8" Page="20" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MARCY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MARIO"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOOTHPICK"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. cheesecake factory vip parking area - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mario and Toothpick pull up to VIP with reefer smoke flowing from the car.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TOOTHPICK</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>How we gonna park the car with all this damn smoke?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Mario</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s cool.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Damn, you see that?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony and Robin are laughing as they walk into restaurant.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Mario (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Ain’t that Hendrix ole girl, Robin?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TOOTHPICK</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah. And that’s ole boy from the radio.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Mario</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tony Sinclair.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You remember when his girl dumped his ass on the radio?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TOOTHPICK</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah but he done come up since then.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Mario</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>So now he with ole girl?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TOOTHPICK</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Look like it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="24" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 3/8" Page="20" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHRISTINE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. CHEESECAKE FACTORY - NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony and Robin are enjoying a lovely dinner.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tony, I want to thank you for accepting my offer for dinner.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The pleasure is all mine.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Suddenly, Christine, Tony’s old girlfriend, comes into view.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey, Mr. Sinclair.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(somewhat surprised)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I hope I’m not interrupting anything?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Tony</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No, not at all.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Is this the new Ms. Sinclair?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Robin, this is Christine.  Christine, Robin.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Nice to meet you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, right.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Suddenly, Christine’s GIRLFRIEND calls her back to her table.  Her eyes say it all, as her girlfriend “CALLS” her again.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Enjoy your evening.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, you too.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What was that all about?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Just someone I went to school with.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What school did you attend?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>FAMU.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Are you serious? I went to FAM too.  What was your major?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mass Communications.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That makes sense. You are in radio.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, but really I had plans of doing something else.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I really wanted to get into production; movies, film, but I got stuck behind the mic at the station.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You know, it’s never too late. It can still happen.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You never know.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Anyway, you have no idea how you saved my life.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You keep saying that. I don’t get it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(very serious look)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The night I called into your show.  The same night, your girlfriend,...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(interrupting her)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I know that part. Actually I got a large following behind that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Go on.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Anyway. I was about to take my life.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I know you were in a bad relationship, but nothing’s worth suicide.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You have no idea of what I was going through. Things started out so nice in the beginning.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="25" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="23" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. HENDRIX’S DINING ROOM - FLASHBACK</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hendrix POV</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Robin sits at a very nice dining room table. She opens a jewelry box and pulls out a very expensive looking bracelet. She’s ecstatic as he leans in to kiss her man.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="26" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="23" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. CHEESECAKE FACTORY - PRESENT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Then it got really crazy.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="27" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="23" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. HENDRIX’S BATHROOM - FLASHBACK</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Robin is on the bathroom floor, crying her eyes out, as the feet of Hendrix step over here and walk away. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She stares after him as mascara and snot run down her face.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She stands up, opening the medicine cabinet and staring at a couple bottle of pills.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="28" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="23" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. DARK ROOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Robin sits in a dark room in front of a glowing radio, listening to Tony’s show.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="29" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="23" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. Radio STATION</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re listening to the quiet storm with Tony Sinclair.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I was about to end it all when I called you. And what you said gave me the strength to leave.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>If the relationship is not working, then you should leave. Let go and let God.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="30" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="24" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. HENDRIX HOUSE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We HEAR those words being repeated over and over again. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Robin scoops up her things, rushing out of the massive home.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="31" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="5/8" Page="24" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. CHEESECAKE FACTORY - present</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to the passing Waiter)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Can you get me two glasses - no a bottle of Riesling?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The Waiter returns with the wine; POURING each of them a glass. He leaves the bottle before walking away.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Robin takes a SIP.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>How is it?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Not bad.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TonY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>So you’re a FAMU Rattler?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(taking another SIP)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Don’t worry. I won’t bite.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(also taking a SIP)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Is that right?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony DOWNS a whole glass.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="32" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="6/8" Page="24" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. robin’s house - NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony is dropping Robin off. They chat at her doorstep.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I must say, I had a really nice time. Thanks for dropping me off. Saved me an Uber.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No problem. We should do this again.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’d like that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The station is having a meet and greet for some new artist next week at </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Oceaner’s</Text>
      <Text>. Would you like to go?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t know. I’ll have to check my schedule and get back to you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat, looking at her cell)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Okay. What time?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They LAUGH.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ll get back to you tomorrow.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sounds good.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She gives him a HUG and a light KISS, then turns and ENTERS her place. Tony just stands there, with a SMILE on his face.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="33" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 5/8" Page="25" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. RADIO STATION - DAY </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>MUSIC TREATMENT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony is doing his thing and is in a very upbeat mood. It’s reflected in his choice of music in today’s rotation. Lovely Day is just ending on the box.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(on the air)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That was Lovely Day and a lovely Day it is. Hey people, I got to tell ya; I’m feeling GREAT today. It’s something about being around good people and good vibes that makes the world look so different.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Let’s keep this positive vibe and fall WAY back to some Sweet Thing, by Chaka Khan. This one goes out to all the sweet things in the ATL; especially one; and she knows who she is.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony plays another song, then sits back daydreaming. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>His cell RINGS; it’s Robin.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>How you doing?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Was that shout out for me?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You better know it. How’s your day going?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Not bad, just trying to wrap up a few things so I can leave a little early.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Are we still on for tonight?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah. I’ve got my nails done, now I’ve need to get a pedicure.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The girl gonna have her hands and feet ready for a brother. Go on,  Ms. FAMU Rattler. You might fool around and bite.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(using one of Tony’s phrases)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Is that right?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony’s PRODUCER is cueing him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey, baby. Gotta get back on the air.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Okay. Enjoy.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A love song plays in the background.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony ends the call and gets back to work, feeling pretty good.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>MUSIC TREATMENT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>INT. RADIO STATION MEET AND GREET PARTY AT </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">OCEANER’S</Text>
      <Text> - NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>MONTAGE of Tony and Robin having a great time at the meet and greet party. The night is filled with nothing but good vibes and good times. It seems like the partying will never end, but finally does.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="34" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 1/8" Page="27" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HENDRIX"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="AllCaps">oceaner’S</Text>
      <Text> Restaurant - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony and Robin are leaving the event at </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Oceaner’s</Text>
      <Text>. A large black Benz is parked up front, with Mario and Toothpick standing in front of it. Mario OPENS the door, and the man’s face inside can’t be seen, because of the SMOKE coming from his cigar. As the SMOKE clears, it reveals the face of a powerfully built man. HENDRIX steps out the car with confidence. He’s nobody to play with.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Hendrix</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Robin)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey, baby. How you doing? I’ve missed you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What are you doing here?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Just out for a minute, </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">coolin</Text>
      <Text>.  It’s good to see you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony looks </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">awkard</Text>
      <Text>.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I see you’ve had dinner. Why don’t you come with me for a drink?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t think so.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(GRABBING her arm)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(cutting in)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Look, I don’t mean any disrespect, but I don’t think the young lady wants to go with you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Toothpick OPENS his jacket, revealing a large handgun.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(still GRABBING her)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I said come on!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Robin breaks free, spraying Hendrix with pepper spray. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony kicks Toothpick in the balls and they RUN.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>How you let him get the drop on you like that? Go get his ass!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mario and Toothpick are making a DASH at Tony and Robin.  Toothpick pulls out his gun, attempting to fire, but almost gets hit by a car.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="35" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 1/8" Page="28" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. TONY’S CAR - NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The pile into the car and Tony floors the pedal.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(shaken and out of breath)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What was that all about?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That was my old boyfriend. The guy I left.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What!?! Do you know who that is!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Of course I do.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s Hendrix. Hendrix!  </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>He’s the largest dope man in Atlanta. In the Southeast. That’s your ex!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She nods.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">(sotto</Text>
      <Text> voce)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Ah MAN!!! What have I gotten myself into?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(holding his hand)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s gonna be okay. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah right.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony weaves through traffic.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>La Vista, coming up next. He doesn’t know where I live. We can go to my place.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I live in a swipe system security building. You can chill there for the night and we’ll get your car in the morning. Hendrix. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">(Sotto</Text>
      <Text> Voce) </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Damn Tony.  What have you gotten yourself into?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="36" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 5/8" Page="29" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. TONY’S APRTMENT - NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony and Robin quickly enter his place. He crosses directly over to his bar area and POURS himself a drink, downing the whole glass.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You want a drink?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m good.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He pours himself another glass and downs another.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(looking around)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Nice place. Do you have a maid?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Nah, just a good momma.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony’s cat comes over and looks at Robin as if who in the hell is this?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(picking Sheba up)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You have a cat?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, that’s Sheba, the lady of the house.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>She’s so cute.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s different for a guy. Most of you guys have big ass dogs.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>She was for my old girlfriend.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He takes another sip of his third glass of wine.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Make yourself at home. You can have my bed. I’ll chill out here on the sofa. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You don’t have to do that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No big deal.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That is so sweet.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do you have a T-shirt and some socks I can borrow?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sure.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He crosses to the bedroom and comes back with something for her to wear.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Here you go.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I really appreciate it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No problem.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She heads to the bedroom to change, when the phone RINGS.  It’s Darien.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ToNY (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hello?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s up, freak?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey D, what’s going on?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="37" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 3/8" Page="30" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="GIRL #1"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="GIRL #1 &amp; GIRL #2"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Darien’s Car - Late Night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We CROSSCUT Tony &amp; Darien, with two WILD THOTS in the car. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Man, I just left Magic City with two dancers.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh for real?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah. These girls are really wild.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Girl #1</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Is that Tony Sinclair from V-105?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, baby.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>GIRL #1 &amp; Girl #2</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(screaming in the phone)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey, Tony!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>See what I mean. I told them I know you and they want to come over.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What, your momma has her boyfriend over again?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>How you know? Anyway, I’m on my way... </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">cool</Text>
      <Text>?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Not tonight.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What!?!  Did I tell you these girls work at Magic City!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, but I’ve had a wild night.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s what we trying to have!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Robin pops out of the bedroom wearing the looking like dessert. Tony is at loss for words.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ToNY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ll call you back.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, man! Call me back!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The call ends.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(with her dress in hand)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do you have a hanger I can put this on?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ll take care of that. Make your self at home. Get some rest.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(giving him a hug)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I will. Good night.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She goes to the room, leaving Tony to settle in on the sofa.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="38" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="32" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Tony’s bedroom - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Robin is trying to settle down and go to sleep. She’s struggling with it; grabbing the other pillow, putting it between her legs. We SEE the desk clock and we see that an hour, now two hours have past and she’s still not asleep.  </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="39" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="32" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. Tony’s living room</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony is out cold on the sofa. He’s awaken when he finds Robin, straddled across him, with nothing but her T-shirt on.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Robin? </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She puts her finger to his lips, then places a gentle kiss.  He is totally taken by surprise, but he likes it; while they fall to the floor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="40" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="32" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. TONY’S LIVING ROOM - MORNING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony is wakes up on the floor naked, completely stretched out. But he’s alone. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He puts on his boxers and looks around the apartment.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She’s gone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Suddenly his phone rings.  </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hello?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Are you awake?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah. What happened to you?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="41" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1" Page="33" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. RoBIN'S HOUSE - morning</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Crosscut of Tony and Robin at her place.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I caught a Uber. I’m at home now.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I could have taken you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You were sleeping so good, I didn’t want to wake you. I had a really nice time last night.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I was beginning to think it was a dream.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No, it wasn’t a dream and I am for real; in spite of the drama from Hendrix. Don’t worry about him.  It’ll be okay.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You sure?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Look, I’ve got to get ready for work.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I hope I can see you again soon?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Have a good one and I’ll talk to you soon. Bye.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They HANG UP.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="42" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="6/8" Page="34" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BRANDON"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. radio station - DAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony is about to go on the air. He’s in with BRANDON, his sales manager.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Brandon</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s up?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s good.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>BRANDON</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Man, that set was BAD the other night.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>BRANDON</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Who was that with you in VIP? She was TOO FINE!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah but that’s a whole long story. I’ve got to get ready for my set.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>BRANDON</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We’ll talk later. Maybe have a drink after work?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text></Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>          TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Cool.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>BRANDON (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(at the door, leaving)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>She got a sister?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony SHAKES his head.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="43" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 5/8" Page="34" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DR. LOVE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HEATHER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HEATHER’S BACKGROUND"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MALE CALLER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MAN CALLER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Radio station - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>MUSIC TREATMENT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony’s set is smoking and he has JENNIFER LOVE, a life coach in the studio. An old school “I Wanna Get Freaky With You” type of song is just coming to an end.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey Atlanta, you’re listening to the mid-day craziness of the Tony Sinclair Show. Today we’re talking about freaky relationships. I have with me in the studio, relationship specialist, Dr. Jennifer Love. How are you doing, Dr. Love?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Dr. Love</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Just great, Tony.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We just played I Wanna Get Freaky With You. What do you think is the importance in relationship of being freaky?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DR. LOVE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Super important. It’s that spice that can keep any relationship fresh and new; no matter how long a couple has been together.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh really?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DR. LOVE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes. The worst thing anyone can do is get caught up in the same dull routine. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You think so?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DR. LOVE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I know so.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dr. Love puts her hand on Tony’s thigh.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DR. LOVE (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Keep it spicy; keep it a little freaky and see how happy both of you will be.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(caught off guard)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Okay hey we got a caller.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HEATHER (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hi, my name is Heather.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hi Heather, what’s your question?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Heather (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m white and my boyfriend is a Black up and coming rapper.  </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HEATHER (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>He likes me to call him the “N” word when we’re making love. Is that okay?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DR. LOVE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>As long as you keep it there and don’t go overboard with it. I think it’ll be fine.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HEATHER’s BACKGROUND (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>See, that’s what’s up!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Okay, next caller.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Male caller</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, I want to talk about guys that get in your business.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Who up in your business man talk to me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MAN CALLER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I mean guys that want to tell your lady what to do. You know, get in your relationship and mess things up. What would you do about that?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I guess I’d have to see about that dude.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MAN CALLER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What do you think about DJ’s that want to give advice and have your girl leave you, then gets dumped on the radio?! What do you think about that!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Maybe, if you loved her right, that wouldn’t have happen.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MAN CALLER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I guess that’s why the whole city heard her leave me and how your girl dumped your ass!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony’s Producer gives the “CUT THE CALL” sign.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Okay, we have to move on to the next caller.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MAN CALLER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I bet you--</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Let’s take a break and when we come back, we’ll have more from Dr. Jennifer Love on this relationship Thursday, on the Tony Sinclair Show.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They cut to commercial.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dr. Love, has a puzzled look on her face and Tony seems somewhat shaken, as we CUT TO:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="44" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3 1/8" Page="37" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. LOCAL GYM - DAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony, Darien and Ken are working out. Tony is bench pressing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Come on man, one more set.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony is struggling with it, and gives up on the set.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s wrong, that’s only 100 pounds?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>My mind’s somewhere else.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s up?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I had some wild shit happening the past few days.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s up?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You remember that fine thang from the club the other night? The one that came up in VIP?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah. She was bad as hell! Cheryl asked me what was up with that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>More than I want. More than I need.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You remember the night me and Christine broke up?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(talking loud)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, she dumped your ass on the radio. The whole city heard you get fired.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Can your ass just chill?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Anyway, she was the chick that called right before Christine.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KeN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No shit? </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I bullshit you not.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Ah man, that’s crazy. You told her to break up with her boyfriend.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It gets even more crazy.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>She was all over you at the club.  Seems like she wants to get with you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>She does; but the dude she broke up with is Hendrix, from the Ghetto Boys.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The Ghetto Boys!?! They sling all the weed, coke and pills, in the ATL; in the Southeast.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>People in the Gym are starting to take in their conversation.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Darien)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You want to tell everybody?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEn</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>My bad.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Man, this is not cool.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Not cool? He came up on us at the Cheesecake Factory with two of his boys the other night. That’s why I couldn’t get with you and the two chicks from Magic City.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(still talking loud)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Man those honey’s were BAD too!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I can’t believe that’s the same girl that called in the night Christine fired your ass.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Even more people are listening to their conversation, some laughing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Man, can you just chill?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It gets worst. This dude calls the station today and called me out.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Man, this is serious. You may need to contact the po </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">po</Text>
      <Text>.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Nah, it’s cool.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No, it’s not cool. Man, you’re a public figure.  You have to be everywhere. You can’t be you; with this guy calling you out like that.  Anything could happen.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Man,...this is crazy. All of this happen, just because she called in and you told her to get rid of ole boy?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What does Robin do?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Something in the mental health field.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>She works in the mental health field and she’s calling in to your show for advice?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s what’s so crazy about all this.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You made need to protect yourself.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What do you mean?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You know - start packing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Nah man...it ain’t like that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s like that with Hendrix.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Darien and Ken, both NOD yes. Even a few of the gym rats listening to their conversation also NOD yes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="45" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 1/8" Page="40" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="LADY #1"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MARIO"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOOTHPICK"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Ext. Gym parking lot - day </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony is approaching his car, when he’s met by Mario and Toothpick.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Mario</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, nagger. Now what you gonna do?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey man, I don’t have no beef with you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TOOTHPICK</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(revealing a gun)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wrong. My man Hendrix wants to see you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>About what?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Mario</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(mimicking Tony)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>About what? Listen at him.  Sounding like a bitch. We getting ready to fuck you up!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TOOTHPICK</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(giving his gun to Mario)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Here. Watch this nagger, while I go get the car.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MARIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I got this.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Toothpick heads for the car, with Mario holding the gun on Tony. Suddenly a group of extremely fine LADIES are coming out of the gym, getting Mario’s attention.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MARIO (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey ladies, what’s up!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Lady #1</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(recognizing Tony)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Aren’t you Tony Sinclair, from     V-105?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>This gives Tony a chance to get the drop on Mario; KICKING him in the balls again.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MARIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(dropping the gun and holding his balls)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh ..I’ll never have kids!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony breaks for his car and flees the parking lot.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="46" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2" Page="41" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. TONY CAR - DAY </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony races through the streets of the ATL, fleeing from Mario and Toothpick.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">(Sotto</Text>
      <Text> voce)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This is crazy.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>His phone RINGS. It’s Robin.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hello?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hi, Tony. You busy?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Just a little bit.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sounds like you’re out of breath.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, I just finished dealing with Twiddle Dee and Twiddle Dumb.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Who?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Two of Hendrix goons.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Are you okay?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m so sorry.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s cool.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I want to see you. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t know about that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I want to make this right.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m supposed to meet my boys Ken and Darien at Magic City, but I don’t have to go.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Did you bump your head? Go out with your boys. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Are you for real?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah. Go on do your thing.  Make it rain. But not too much.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s what’s up. I really like your style.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(coining Tony’s old saying again)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Is that right?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah. That’s right.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They both LAUGH.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ll call you later.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I hope so.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Be careful.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Okay. I will.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We’ll talk later. Bye.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Damn.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He almost HITS a car.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">(Sotto</Text>
      <Text> voce)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This is too much.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="47" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="5/8" Page="43" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="SADE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Ext. hallway at tonY’s condo - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony is coming out of his condo, suited and booted to the tee. He passes Sade in her door, as before; with a bottle of wine and two glasses. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>SaDE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Damn! You always got on the best oils! And looking good too!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thanks.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>SADE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(pouring herself another glass of wine)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You want to come in for a sip before you head out?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Love to; but I’m running late.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He heads towards the elevator.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>SadE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(admiring his ass)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Well go on with you, badass.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="48" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 1/8" Page="44" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. magic city Strip club - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A DANCERS’s ass shakes to the music. Ken and Darien are downing some brews, when Tony walks in. Its obvious his nerves are fried. He crosses over to them, sitting with his back to the wall.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s up, man?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You got it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KeN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Why you getting all in the corner, with your back to the wall?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You acting like that dude in Menace to Society.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Nothing wrong with have a strong wall to your back. Like Malcolm.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Man, you alright? You don’t look good.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t feel good.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s wrong?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Them boys still on my jock.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(talking loud again)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Who, Hendrix?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You got one more time to talk so damn loud.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Man, you gonna have to do something about this.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s cool.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s not cool. You need to contact the police.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Damn right.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I must be right, if Darien agrees with me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(with a funny look)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s cool.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KeN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Nah man, it’s not cool. You’re gonna have to get you some security or a piece. You’ve got too much going on to carry on like this.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You guy’s are making this a bigger deal than it is. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m not worried about Twiddle Dee, Twiddle Dumb or Hendrix.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Darien’s two STRIPPER FRIENDS, make their way over to the table. They are total knock outs, and begin to dance all over Tony and Ken.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Maybe this will make you feel better.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>THe girls continue to dance. The guys are having a good time.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Tony)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Like that; don’t ya?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony and Ken have big SMILES on their faces.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Man; I’m gonna go home and take this out on my girl.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Suddenly, a loud POP from a bottle of Champagne has Tony hitting the floor. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A group of WAITERS clap, celebrating someone’s birthday.  </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Everybody looking at Tony like a jackass.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="49" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="4/8" Page="46" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. TONY’S APaRTMENT LOBBY - NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>WE SEE a totally shaken Tony, walking into the lobby of his apartment complex. To his surprise, Robin is there.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Robin?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Are you okay?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah. I forgot about us getting together.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(rubbing sweat from him)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Why are you sweating like this?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s been a long day.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Come on.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="50" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="46" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>MUSIC TREATMENT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="51" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="46" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. TONY’S APARTMENT Bathroom - NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony and Robin taking are in the tub together. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="52" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 1/8" Page="47" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. TonY'S BEDROOM</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Robin is on top giving Tony more reasons to sweat as she puts it on him. She pins him to the bed, forcing him deeper and deeper into her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>LATER
</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The are relaxed as they cuddle in bed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(rubbing his chest)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This is so nice.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re so nice.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I can’t believe we’re like this.  Can you?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What do you mean?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Why did you get with me?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Why did you get with me?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It was your booty.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She give him a play slap.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Be serious.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Seriously it was your booty.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You are so crazy.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Why did you pick me?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Are you kidding. Why wouldn’t any woman want to be with you? You’re so sweet.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah right.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I mean it. I knew that from the first time I talked to you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>When?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>When I called into the station that night.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do we have to talk about that?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Is that still a sour spot?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>A little bit.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I was going through so much.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You mean with Hendrix? How’d you get with a dude like him?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You know like on Oprah; they talk about how women are in abusive relationships and know they need to leave, but can’t? That’s how I was.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>He was so sweet and laid back when we first got together. Then all of a sudden things changed when I moved in. He got super controlling.  I couldn’t even go to the bathroom, without him wanting to know where I was and what I was doing. I couldn’t even drive myself to work anymore. He’d drop me off and pick me up. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Are you serious?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Then he started putting his hands on me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>He hit you!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="53" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="5/8" Page="49" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHRISTINE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. HEnDRIX’s HOUSE - FLASHBACK</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The scene plays out as Robin describes it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIn (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Grabbing me and pinning me down, more than anything. He used to say it didn’t make sense to bruise up a peach then try to eat it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>PRESENT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s some sick, shi,...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah you’re right. But that’s what I was going through the night I called you. That night I got the courage to leave and since then, I’ve been able to really live again.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony holds her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>When I’m with you, I feel safe.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text>FADE OUT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="54" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="4/8" Page="49" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHRISTINE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. TONY’S APARTMENT LOBBY - DAY </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony is entering his building and to his surprise, he’s met by Christine.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Christine? Whatcha doing here?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I ran into Darien and he told me about your new place.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>He did huh?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I just wanted to check it out.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The building CONCIERGE is checking out Christine’s figure.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Come on up.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="55" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 7/8" Page="50" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHRISTINE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. TONY’S APARTMENT - DAY </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony and Christine walk into the apartment.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This is nice. I guess all those late night shifts paid off.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Okay. My bad.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Suddenly Tony’s cat enters the room.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(trying to GRAB her)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sheba. You still have her?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Sheba RUNS away and Tony tries to catch her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Am I interrupting something?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Well, I kinda...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He takes off one shirt and puts on another. Christine takes in how cut Tony has gotten.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(admiring Tony’s build)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Damn you been working out?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(fanning modesty)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>A little bit.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(crossing over to Tony, touching his shoulder)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You sure have.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She gives him a kiss on his neck.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What are you doing!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m just checking out what’s mine.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She starts up again, when Robin open the door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What the fuck? </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Honey, this is for real not what you think.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Christine)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I know you. You’re the lady from the restaurant. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s right. I’m his woman.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Really?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This is my old girl, Christine.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Christine?  The one that dumped you on the radio the night I called in?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You got to be lying.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What!?! You called in?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Honey, please. Let me explain.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(looking at his exposed chest)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It looks like you’re already doing that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Robin SLAMS the door on the way out.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tony, I’m so sorry.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(grabbing her arm)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You need to go!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="56" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="52" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Ext. Tony’s apartment hallway - day </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony is escorting Christine out and trying to catch Robin on the elevator. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Robin, please!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The elevator CLOSES. Tony and Christine catch the next one.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="57" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="4/8" Page="52" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CONCIERGE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Tony’s apartment lobby - day </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony and Christine have made it to the lobby. Robin’s car BURNS rubber as she pulls off.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Tony</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Christine)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You gotta go.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony is not happy as he approaches the Concierge area.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Concierge</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Tony)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Is everything alright, Mr. Sinclair?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t want you letting anyone up to see me without my knowledge! You got me!?! NOBODY!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="58" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="52" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="SADE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Ext. Tony’s apartment hallway - day </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony exits the elevator and is approaching his apartment, when Sade pops out of her place.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>SADE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(with a bottle of wine and two glasses, like before)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey, stranger. What’s going on?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(taking one of her wine glasses)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Give me some of that wine.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>SADE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(pouring)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sure. Come on in.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="59" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="7/8" Page="53" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="SADE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. SADE’s LIVING ROOM </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony sits up on the couch super animated as he vents to Sade.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Then the next thing you know my old girl, Christine, shows up and all hell breaks loose.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>SADE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tony, the first thing you’re gonna have to do is just relax. Take some quality time by yourself and think things through. And the main thing you’re gonna have to do is pray on it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>SADE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You heard me. There’s power in prayer. God’s not gonna put more on you than you can handle.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He DOWNS the last of his glass.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>SADE (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(taking his glass)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Now, get your ass out a here.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He crosses to leave.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(giving her a HUG)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thanks, Sharde’, I mean Sade.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>SADE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Boy, please. Do what I said you heard me?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony has a look of resolve on his face.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="60" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="53" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. RadIO STATION - Day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony’s working but he’s obviously not into it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="61" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="7/8" Page="53" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Local sports bar - dusk</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Ken and Darien sit a table drinking. Tony walks in and stomps over to their table.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s up?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(not happy)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s up is my foot about to go up in yo ass!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What you talking about man!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Man, I’d stomp your ass if we weren’t in this bar! Where you get off running your mouth to Christine; telling her where I live!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This little dumb ass always running off at the mouth, at the wrong time!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Man, I’m,...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You ain’t got NOTHING to say to me! You just need to learn how to shut the hell up. You hear me!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony angrily leaves the bar.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="62" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="54" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HENDRIX"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. tONY’S living room - NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>MUSIC TREATMENT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony is alone, listening to some music, chilling. He picks up the phone and dials Robin’s number.  She doesn’t answer. He dials again. Nothing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He throws the phone onto the sofa.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He finds himself asleep on the sofa. The nearby clock shows 3 a.</Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">m</Text>
      <Text>., when his phone RINGS. It’s Robin.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hello?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="63" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1" Page="55" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HENDRIX"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. RoBIN'S HOUSE - Late Night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>CROSSCUT Tony &amp; Robin.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RoBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text>BACK TO:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Are you okay!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I need your help.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s wrong?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text>Back TO:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Suddenly, Hendrix takes the phone from her and we’re now at Robin’s place.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah partner; we have some business to finish; face to face.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Who the hell you think you are, having my ho bitch leaving me?  Don’t nobody leave me, nagger!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey man, I don’t want,...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t give a DAMN what you want!  You need to meet me at the Wilson’s Brothers Lumber Yard on Bankhead in an hour. And your ass better be by yourself. Otherwise the next time you see ole girl, will be in some dog food. You understand me!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, man. I understand.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="64" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="56" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MARIO"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Ext. Wilson’s brothers lumber yard - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A large SUV is parked, with its bright lights on.  Tony’s car comes into view and parks. He nervously gets out and stands next to his car. Mario and Toothpick are in the SUV and slowly approach him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MARIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s up, bitch!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>How’s your nuts?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mario HITS Tony over the head with his gun, knocking him out.  Toothpick puts a bag over his head. They drag him to the their SUV.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="65" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2" Page="56" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HENDRIX"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MARIO"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Hendrix’s house - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mario and Toothpick are dragging Tony into Hendrix’s house.  They remove the bag from his head and he SEES Robin, who’s dressed in a very sexy Victory’s Secret outfit.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Tony</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Robin?  I’m so sorry. It wasn’t what you thought with me and Christine.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mario </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">hiys</Text>
      <Text> him in the stomach.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MARIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Be still. We just getting started.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hendrix struts in, smoking a fat cigar. He’s accompanied by two even larger goons.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This is so sweet. So sweet that it’s killing me,...and you too.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Because of you, my woman left me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m not your woman!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hendrix grabs Robin, then begins to choke her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Choke a bitch; they’ll love you.  Let her breathe and then she’ll leave.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mario, Toothpick and the two Goons LAUGH and agree with Hendrix.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(applying more pressure to Robin’s neck)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Maybe I should’ve kept chocking your ass.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(in Portuguese)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re a real big man, Hendrix.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(losing his cool, also in Portuguese)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Say that again! You judging me!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He punches Tony.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ll beat your ass too!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(putting his gun in Tony’s mouth)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ll blow your ass all over this wall.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Robin RUNS over to Hendrix and begins to KISS him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(KISSING Hendrix)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Baby, please don’t hurt him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(removing the gun from Tony’s mouth)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ll let him live, but you better not ever try to leave me again.  You hear me!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I hear you baby. I hear you!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ll let your punk ass live.  You’re lucky my girl begged for yo life!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I won’t, baby. I’ll never leave you again.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Cool, now go put some clothes on so we can go get something to eat.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Robin leaves the room and Hendrix gives the gun to Mario.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX (CONT'D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(in Mario &amp; Toothpick’s ear)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Get rid of em. Make it look like a suicide or something.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Everyone bounces, leaving Hendrix alone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>His phone RINGS.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(reluctantly answering)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="66" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 2/8" Page="58" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HENDRIX"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MOSTAFA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. High rise apartment - INTERCUT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Mostafa</Text>
      <Text> (45-50)a powerfully built man of Arabian descent, looks out over a breathtaking view of the city.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="AllCaps">Mostafa</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Hendrix)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re spending a lot of time with your personal life, instead of our business, Hendrix.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="AllCaps">MOSTAFA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The walls have ears.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hendrix hits his blunt and sips from some cognac.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t have time for this shit you talking about!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Mostafa</Text>
      <Text> motions for one of his assistance to bring him a tray of cocaine.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="AllCaps">MOSTAFA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You work for me; I tell you what you have time for.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Man fuck you!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="AllCaps">MOSTAFA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(calmly, as he snorts the cocaine)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Where’s my money?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Don’t worry about it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Mostafa</Text>
      <Text> starts to lose his cool.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="AllCaps">MOSTAFA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(speaking in Farsi language)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Where’s my fucking money!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text> </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Mostofa</Text>
      <Text> knocks the tray of coke from his assistants hand.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(also speaking in Farsi)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I got your fucking money!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="AllCaps">MOSTAFA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Very good.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He hangs up. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hendrix, alone in his living room, is deep in thought.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="67" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="59" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Ext. HenDRIX HOUSE - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hendrix and Robin approach his car.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Darien and Ken are parked across the street, watching.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="68" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="59" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. Darien’s Car - Night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(with gun in hand)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Let’s cap his ass.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Be cool.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hendrix and Robin pull off. Soon after, Tony, Mario, Toothpick and the two Goons come out, putting Tony in the SUV. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They pull off. Ken &amp; Darien follow.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="69" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 3/8" Page="59" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HENDRIX"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MARIO"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOOTHPICK"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. CONSTRUCTION AREA - NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The SUV pulls up with Tony inside.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TOOTHPICK</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Let’s make this quick.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MARIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, let’s put his ass in a wall, like they did on the Soprano’s.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TOOTHPICK</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Shut the FUCK up and let’s do this!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A they start to get out the truck, Darien &amp; Ken SHOOT their lights out. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Everyone from the SUV scatters as SHOTS are fired. The two Goons get hit in the ass. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony KICKS Mario in the balls again, Toothpick runs, slips and falls, losing his gun in the dark.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony, Ken and Darien start </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">tieing</Text>
      <Text> the two Goons up, along with Mario and Toothpick. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(putting the Goons in the SUV)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Come on D, help me with these dudes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I can’t get no damn blood on my jacket. This suede.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(slapping him on the head)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Man, come on.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s your last time hitting me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Suddenly, Mario’s cell phone RINGS. It’s Hendrix. Tony hits speakerphone puts the phone to Mario’s mouth.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Mario)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You know what to say.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You guys straight?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony puts a gun to Mario’s dome.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MARIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, we’re cool.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Did you pick up my package?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MARIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, we got it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Well then bring your ass to the house, now!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="70" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="5/8" Page="61" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HENDRIX"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. HENDRIX HOUSE - NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hendrix is getting faded, drinking Hennessy straight from the bottle and smoking a blunt. Robin is next to him and he’s very relaxed. There’s a KNOCK at the door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">(Sotto</Text>
      <Text> voce)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>About time them motherfuckers...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He opens the door, revealing Mario. Suddenly, he’s bum rushed by Tony, Ken and Darien. SHOTS are fired. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hendrix GRABS Robin and DASHES for his car. Tony and his crew are in pursuit. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Them motherfuckers getting away!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Ken &amp; Darien)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ll follow em. I need you two to get the police.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You heard me. Go!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="71" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="5/8" Page="61" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HENDRIX"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MARIO"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOOTHPICK"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Ext: busy atlanta streets - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hendrix is driving CRAZY, weaving in and out of traffic with his foot on the gas. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Robin is in the passenger seat, in tears, as Hendrix waves a large chrome pistol around. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>His phone RINGS and he answers it through the car phone speaker phone. It’s Mario and Toothpick.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Where you motherfuckers at!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TOOTHPICK (v.o.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We in the car.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You got my product?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TOOTHPICK</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s at the spot.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We almost there!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mario is driving crazy, almost hitting someone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Mario</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">shitttt</Text>
      <Text>!!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TOOTHPICK</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Watch it;...motherfucker!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="72" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="62" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Ext. Kid’s world day care - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hendrix’s and Mario’s cars are parked.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="73" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="7/8" Page="62" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HENDRIX"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TOOTHPICK"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Kid’s WORLD DAY CARE - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mario and Toothpick are packing up drugs that are hidden in children’s back to school supplies. Hendrix has Robin tied to a chair with tape on her mouth. He SMOKES a blunt.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(pulling on a blunt. Testing the product)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, this some good shit here.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>How much we got?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TOOTHPICK</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Five hundred Ps.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Nice.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hendrix crosses over to Robin.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Robin)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You see this? Five hundred pounds of Hydro. That’s so much money, I can’t even count it all.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Robin is not impressed. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(taking the tape off her mouth.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What? You want to say something? What you looking at?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Nothing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(with the gun to her head)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I shoulda killed your ass a long time ago.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="74" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="63" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHRISTINE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="FEMALE VOICE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HENDRIX"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MALE VOICE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Darien’s Car - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Ken and Darien are driving fast when one of Atlanta’s finest spots them; puts his lights on and pulls them over.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="75" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 6/8" Page="63" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHRISTINE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HENDRIX"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. KID’S WORLD DAY CARE - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hendrix is feeling no pain from the effects of the weed and begins to get into a reminiscing rage with Robin.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You coulda had everything. The houses, the cars all the money. But you gave it up because of what a STUPID motherfucker on the radio told ya! I loved you. I still love you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hendrix PACES the floor, waving the gun; then back in Robin’s face.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And on top of it all, his girl called in and broke up with his dumb ass on the radio.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mario, Toothpick and Hendrix; all have a big LAUGH.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(in Robin’s face)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You a dumb bitch!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat, to Mario and Toothpick)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Come on and pack this shit up! We got a plane to catch!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(spitting in his face and trying to break free)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You call THIS love!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>This causes Hendrix to go into a rage. He MOTIONS to HIT her with his gun; when we HEAR: </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hold it!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>It’s Tony, with gun in hand and has the drop on Hendrix and crew.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Hendrix)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Who’s the dumb bitch now?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Hendrix and his Crew)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Drop it. Right now!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They drop their guns.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony kicks the guns to the side and begins to UNTIE Robin.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Robin)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Are you okay?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She nods.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Robin, I am so sorry.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Me too.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I should have told you about Christine that night at the Cheesecake Factory.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>She don’t mean nothing to me now.  She’s my past.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>It’s Christine, standing the doorway, with a HUGE gun in hand.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>So, I’m your past, huh?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She slowly SLIDES Hendrix, Toothpick and Mario, their guns. Hendrix, crosses over to Christine; giving her a gentle KISS on the lips.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Christine)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Nice work, baby.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The worst thing you can EVER do, is think someone’s dumber than you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="76" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="65" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHRISTINE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="HENDRIX"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MOSTAFA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. chEESECAKE FACTORY VIP PARKING AREA - FLASHBACK</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>That first night Tony met Robin for dinner at the Cheesecake Factory...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah; you up in the Cheesecake Factory, trying to put the move on my girl and I did the same thang with yours.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A teary-eyed Christine, comes into view. Hendrix is exiting his car, as Christine passes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>HENDRIX</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey, baby girl, you okay?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="77" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 2/8" Page="65" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHRISTINE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MOSTAFA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. Kid'S WORLD DAY CARE - PRESENT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Back to Kid’s World. Hendrix and his Crew have re-tied up Robin and tied up Tony as well.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(getting tied up)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Are you serious?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I knew that night; you wasn’t SHIT Tony. I stuck with your ass when you didn’t have nothing!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHRISTINE (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I paid most of the bills. I paid most of the rent. I was a GOOD woman to you! And what did your sorry ass do!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Work!!! I worked Christine!!! That’s how I got to where I am. I put in the work!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Christine has a sour look on her face.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You didn’t want to wait for a brother to come up. Being a GOOD woman means, hanging in there; doing what it takes to help a man make it. You didn’t do that, Christine.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Christine’s emotions start to get the best of her. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Out of nowhere, slow clapping.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>It’s </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Mostafa</Text>
      <Text> and his GUYS.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="AllCaps">MOSTAFA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That was so sweet and touching.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Hendrix)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Going somewhere?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Mostafa’s</Text>
      <Text> GUY’S slide up on </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">on</Text>
      <Text> Hendrix and his crew.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Mostofa</Text>
      <Text> </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">meaders</Text>
      <Text> over to Hendrix.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="AllCaps">MOSTAFA</Text>
      <Text> (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I was born at night; but not last night.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Suddenly POLICE KICK in the door. Shots are fired, back and forth between the Police, Hendrix, </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Mostafa</Text>
      <Text> and his Crew; as they try to flee. Gunfire is BLAZING. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Hendrix takes one final shot at Robin as he makes an attempt to leave. Even though Tony is tied up; he finds a way to LEAP to his feet and block Hendrix’s shot. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony is hit.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="78" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="5/8" Page="66" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHERYL"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DOCTOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. HOSPITAL WAITING ROOM AREA - NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Darien, Ken, and a blood covered Robin; are all patiently waiting. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Cheryl enters, giving Ken a HUG.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERYL</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Is he okay?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We don’t know yet, but it doesn’t look good.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A DOCTOR comes into view.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>How is he doctor?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Doctor</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>He’s in critical condition. He has a bullet lodged very close to his heart.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>So what does that mean??</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DOCTOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s too early to say. At this point it’s touch and go.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="79" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="67" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHERYL"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. Hospital ICU - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>TIME LAPS MONTAGE of Tony losing a lot of blood in the ICU. It’s an extremely touch and go situation with the ICU team appearing to lose him at one point, then suddenly bring him back.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="80" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="6/8" Page="67" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHERYL"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. HOSPITAL WAITING ROOM AREA </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Everyone sits in the waiting room deep in her own thoughts. Reminiscing about the good and bad times.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Suddenly Darien who loses it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Robin)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s your damn fault!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Robin doesn’t say a word.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You knew you were mixed up with a dope boy when you called into the radio station!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(a beat)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You knew that, when you brought your ass up in VIP at the club!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CHERYL</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Darien!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(trying to compose himself)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Me and Tony been friends since the first grade.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Darien starts to cry. Cheryl holds his hand, then gives him a HUG.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>MONTAGE </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>EXT. ELEMENTARY SCHOOL</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Darien and Tony playing at school.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="81" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="68" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. COLLEGE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Darien and Tony in a frat house pledging.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="82" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="68" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="NURSE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="AllCaps">v105</Text>
      <Text>.5 RADIO STATION</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Darien, Tony and the rest of their crew standing outside the radio station taking pics.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="83" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="68" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="NURSE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. ROBIN’S HOUSE - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>WE SEE Robin HOLDING the picture of Tony and the Gang, as she turns off the light, holding a pillow; trying painstakingly, to go to sleep.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="84" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 5/8" Page="68" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="NURSE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. TONY’S HOSPITAL ROOM - PRESENT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We pick up with a shot of that same picture on the table next to Tony’s bed. Darien and Ken are bedside, watching a Hawks game and eating a pizza.  The Hawks score and they are all into it. Suddenly, a NURSE pops in.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Nurse</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey guys, I’m gonna have to ask you to tone it down; Just a little bit.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No problem.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>My bad. That </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Millsap</Text>
      <Text> is a beast though!!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The Nurse motions for them to tone it down again.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>NURSE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I know you guys are having a good time, but visiting hours are almost over.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, you mofo’s need to cut out all that damn noise.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The guys and the Nurse are SPEECHLESS as they CROSS to his bedside. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Man, I can’t believe you’re up!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(patting Tony on shoulder)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Me either.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Darien starts to CRY.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Cut out all that damn crying, like a bitch! You been doing that ever since I got here.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I was halfway out, but I could hear yo ass, talking bout, “He’s been my best friend since we were in the first grade”</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They all LAUGH.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>NURSE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>So how do you feel?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m alive, surrounded by my friends. God is good.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>NURSE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(crossing to leave)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Let me get a doctor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s good to see you back, man.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That was some wild shit we went through that night.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t remember much.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Man, it was off the chain!!! I know you remember how we had your boy Hendrix hemmed up in that Day Care, he was using for his stash place?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="85" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="70" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. KiD'S WORLD DAY CARE - FLASHBACK</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony walks in with his pistol trained on Hendrix.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Then your old girl, Christine, got the drop on you. Come to find out she and ole boy was working you </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">together</Text>
      <Text>.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="86" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="70" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. TONY’S HOSPITAL ROOM - PRESENT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah,...That’s when it get’s unclear.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s when you got shot.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, that’s when Hendrix capped yo ass.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="87" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="70" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. KiD'S WORLD DAY CARE - FLASHBACK</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony leaps into harms way, still tied to the chair, taking the bullet to defend Robin.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You was trying to protect Robin and you got hit.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="88" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="70" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. TONY’S HOSPITAL ROOM - PRESENT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What happened to Christine and </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hendrix?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="89" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="70" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Kid'S WORLD DAY CARE - FLASHBACK</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The Police rush the room.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s when the police came in and arrested Hendrix and his boys; and your girl Christine.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The Police cuff Hendrix, Christine and the entire gang before taking them off to jail.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="90" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1" Page="71" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DARIEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="DOCTOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="KEN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. Tony’s hosPITAL ROOM - PRESENt</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Christine helped Hendrix shoot me!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hurt people, hurt people.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Where’s Robin?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Both Darien and Ken have a funny look.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Man, you know; a lot happened and you’ve been out of it for a while.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>She bounced man.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(trying to RAISE UP)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>She what!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They come to his aide.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>KEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Like I said; there was a lot that happened.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DARIEN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I guess I said some things I shouldn’t have.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s not the first time.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>It’s obvious Tony’s still in pain; both physically and mentally. The nurse reenters, along with a doctor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>DOCTOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(to Ken &amp; Darien)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I think your friends need to let you get some rest.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The nurse makes adjustments to Tony’s pillow and checks his vital signs; as Darien and Ken cross to leave. We HOLD on Darien looking at Tony at the door; however, Tony doesn’t acknowledge him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="91" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="72" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. HOSPITAL REHABILITATION AREA - DAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony is doing intense rehabilitation in hopes of regaining mobility. He’s being assisted by a TRAINER.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="92" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="72" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="OPERATOR RECORDING"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. TONY’S BEDROOM - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He’s on the phone, trying to call Robin, but we HEAR.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>OPERATOR recording (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The number you have dialed is no longer in service. Please check the number and try again. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony tosses the phone to the side, depressed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>MONTAGE </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="93" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="72" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. BaPTIST CHURCH</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony reads the Bible at a church then attending a lively service at a powerful Baptist Church. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="94" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="72" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BLACK BILL GATES"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="FEMALE LISTNER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="FRANKIE J"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MAN CALLER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. MASJID</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony sits alone reading a Qur’an.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony is in a congregation making salat (prayer).</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Afterwards the brothers greet each other and he seems truly happy and at peace.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="95" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 2/8" Page="72" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BLACK BILL GATES"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="FEMALE LISTNER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="FRANKIE J"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MAN CALLER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Ext./INT. radio station - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Frankie J is in the middle of his show.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>FRANKIE J</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s the latest hit from my man Drake. Hey Atlanta; I’m about to wrap it up; but before I go; I’ve got a special announcement. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>As you all know, my man Tony Sinclair was shot several months ago and we almost lost him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Well I’m, happy to say he’s back on the air!!! Okay, Atlanta; let’s give a warm welcome back to MY MAN!!! Tony Sinclair!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony leans into the mike.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hello, Atlanta!!! You’re on the air with Tony Sinclair!!! </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Darien sits in the back, clapping it up for his long time friend.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I must humbly say it is great to be back.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Let me hear from my people.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(taking a call)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re on the air, with Tony Sinclair; what’s on your mind!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Female listner</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hi, Tony.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hello!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>FEMALE LISTNER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This is Carmen. I want to let you know we’ve missed you and we’re so glad you’re back.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thank you so much; I’m glad to be back!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Man CALLER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey bro, this DJ Black Bill Gates.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>My brother! It’s so good to hear from you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Black Bill Gates</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We thought we lost you, brother. Glad you pulled through.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="96" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 4/8" Page="73" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="A GAY MALE CALLER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ANOTHER FEMALE CALLER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="FEMALE CALLER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MARCUS"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="NEXT CALLER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT./INT. Robin’s car - day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Robin is on the road. She HEARS Tony on the radio and tries to dial in, but gets the ALL CIRCUITS ARE BUSY notice; so she tries again. This time she gets “Welcome to the V105.5 Comment line. If you have a comment, feel free to give your name and a brief comment.”</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She hangs up and tries again.  </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text>Back To:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Next CALLER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(really sexy female caller)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hi, Tony.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>How you doing?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>NEXT CALLER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do you have Bryson Tiller tickets?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes I do. I’ll be giving those away in the next hour so keep tuning in!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>A gay male caller</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hi, Tony; This is Marcus.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s up, Marcus?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Marcus</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I just want to give a shout out to all my friends in town for the Black Gay Pride weekend.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Cool, next caller.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Another female caller</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(somewhat reserved)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hi, Tony, I glad you’re feeling okay.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thank you. Thank you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>FeMALE CALLER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I want to ask your advise.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Go ahead.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>FEMALE CALLER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What should a woman do when she’s made a mess out of getting to know the best man she’s ever known in her life?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t know. What do ya mean?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>FEMALE CALLER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I mean, when she not only puts herself in danger; but him and his friends. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Your voice sounds familiar.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>FEMALE CALLER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It should.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Is this....?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="97" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="6/8" Page="75" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT./INT. RoBIN'S CAR - Day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We have a CROSSCUT of Robin and Tony.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(cutting him off)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Don’t say I was wrong for everything I did and how I did it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>There’s so much silence, the PRODUCER starts some background music. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Where are you!?!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RoBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m on the road. When I heard your voice I had to call in and apologize.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony is speechless.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What I did to you, to us, was wrong. Bringing you into my situation was really not right.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Robin is DRIVING like a wild woman, as she talks to Tony.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It almost cost you your life and mine.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>WE SEE LISTENERS all over the City tuning in.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No one has ever treated me like you did. I just want another chance.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="98" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="76" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. Waffle House</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A bunch of people stand around a car, hanging on every word.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="99" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="76" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. LaUNDRY MAT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Two college kids share headphones waiting to hear what happens next.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text>Back To:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I just don’t know. I just don’t know. What we went through was a lot.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="100" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="6/8" Page="76" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="PRODUCER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INt. RobiN'S CAR - Day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We have a CLOSE UP of Robin; still on the phone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RoBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>If you can tell me no to my face, I’ll never bother you again.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We have a TIGHT SHOT of Tony, deep in thought, when suddenly, there’s a KNOCK on the glass window to his Studio. Tony looks up to see Robin.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The PRODUCER is eating this up.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Producer</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">(sotto</Text>
      <Text> voce)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The ratings are gonna be through the roof!!!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Robin ENTERS the studio and they EMBRACE and KISS. The PRODUCER finds her a chair and a set of headphones.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey Atlanta, I don’t know what to say. I wasn’t expecting this kinda come back! The girl that got all of this started almost four years ago and has my heart POUNDING EVERYDAY; is right here in the station with me. I don’t know what to say.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Darien is looking on, with a big SMILE, NODDING YES, take her back.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="101" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="77" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. ATLANTA </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>LISTENERS all over the City saying, TAKE HER BACK. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="102" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="77" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. radio STATION</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony gets Twitter hits by the thousands saying; TAKE HER BACK. They EMBRACE and KISS once more.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="103" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="6/8" Page="77" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name=""></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="FEMALE CALLER"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ROBIN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TONY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. Radio Station - 6 months later - night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony and Robin are on the air talking to callers. A banner on the wall for the Tony &amp; Robin show.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TONY (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Because of all the traction Robin and I got from our coming back together and the fact she’s a mental health doctor, it was just natural for us to get our own relationship show.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Tony</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(on the air)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You on the air with Tony Sinclair and Dr. Robin.  What’s on your mind?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>FemALE CALLER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This is my first time ever calling in to a radio station.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ROBIN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s okay, go right ahead.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>FEMALE CALLER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m in a really bad relationship that is not only abusive physically, but mentally as well.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What I want to know is; what should I do?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Tony and Robin, both look at each other. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>THE END</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text>Fade Out:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
